by New Anderia » Mon May 10, 2021 4:04 pm

Laka Strolistandiler wrote:Eh, don’t wanna be threadjacking, but I’d really enjoy joining a good alliance. One where the guys don’t wage war on each other extremely trigger-happily.

Speaking of cliches, had anyone mentioned absurd military vehicles or doctrines? Laka has one: a suicidal last stand that will turn the country (and a large part of the world) into a barely inhabitable irradiated wasteland with an enormous chemical and biological fallout after using a shit ton of WMDs on our own soil.

I think my nation has sort of the antithesis of this sort of doctrine, we've got plenty of plans for getting our shit kicked in in a military conflict, but we don't have any well-developed plans that involve actually losing, outside of a Dead Hand system to automate nuclear strikes should we go down first. It's part of why my country never invested heavily into persistent nerve agents like VX for area denial purposes, preferring G-series agents that dissipate relatively rapidly.
The thing with "absurd" military tech/doctrine/whatever is that it's usually pretty obvious even to laymen like myself why an idea is absurd, and why it shouldn't be used or adhered to. What's odd is how little that seems to dissuade people from militarywank.
